  "tool_calls": [
    {
      "name": "Bash",
      "args": {
        "command": "stm32 debug read-peripheral GPIOA",
        "description": "Read GPIOA peripheral registers to check MODER for USART2 pins PA2/PA3"
      }
    }
  ],
  "final_text": "I'll read the GPIOA peripheral (USART2 uses PA2/TX and PA3/RX on the NUCLEO-L476RG) to check the `MODER` fields for those pins.\n**No \u2014 PA2 and PA3 are not in Alternate Function mode.** Here's the full picture from the live register read:\n\n### `GPIOA MODER` \u2014 PA2 (TX) and PA3 (RX)\n\n| Pin | `MODER` value | Meaning | Required |\n|-----|--------------|---------|----------|\n| PA2 (USART2 TX) | `3` (`0b11`) | **Analog** | `2` (`0b10`) = Alternate Function |\n| PA3 (USART2 RX) | `3` (`0b11`) | **Analog** | `2` (`0b10`) = Alternate Function |\n\n### `GPIOA AFRL` \u2014 AF selection for PA2 and PA3\n\n| Pin | `AFRL` value | Meaning | Required |\n|-----|-------------|---------|----------|\n| PA2 | `0xF` (15) | AF15 | `0x7` (7) = USART2 |\n| PA3 | `0xF` (15) | AF15 | `0x7` (7) = USART2 |\n\n### Summary\n\nBoth pins have a **double misconfiguration**:\n\n1. **Wrong mode** \u2014 `MODER` is `0b11` (Analog) instead of `0b10` (Alternate Function). The GPIO is floating/disconnected from the peripheral bus.\n2. **Wrong AF selection** \u2014 `AFRL` is `0xF` (AF15) instead of `0x7` (AF7), which is the USART2 mapping on the L476RG.\n\nUntil both are corrected, USART2 will receive no clock edges and TX will not drive the pin. The fix in your init code is:\n\n```c\n// Enable GPIOA clock first (if not already done)\nRCC->AHB2ENR |= RCC_AHB2ENR_GPIOAEN;\n\n// Set PA2 and PA3 to Alternate Function mode (MODER = 0b10)\nGPIOA->MODER &= ~(GPIO_MODER_MODE2 | GPIO_MODER_MODE3);\nGPIOA->MODER |=  (GPIO_MODER_MODE2_1 | GPIO_MODER_MODE3_1);\n\n// Select AF7 (USART2) on PA2 and PA3\nGPIOA->AFR[0] &= ~(GPIO_AFRL_AFSEL2 | GPIO_AFRL_AFSEL3);\nGPIOA->AFR[0] |=  (7UL << GPIO_AFRL_AFSEL2_Pos) | (7UL << GPIO_AFRL_AFSEL3_Pos);\n```"
}